item.title: Simple Crystal
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: The Simple Crystal Straight Champagne Glass by Deborah Ehrlich, is a stemless flute that is mouth-blown, hand-cut and polished by expert artisans in Sweden. As with Ehrlich’s other Simple Crystal series of glassware, the Straight Champagne glass is paper thin, clear as water, and absolutely flawless. A beautifully simplified design with a contemporary twist, yet instantly recognizable due to its archetypal silhouette and perfect proportions.
item.excerpt:encoded: Made of non-lead Swedish crystal, and finished by Ehrlich's signature with a diamond-tipped pen on the underside.

item.title: Soy Sauce
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.excerpt:encoded: THE Soy Sauce Cruet is also perfect for olive oil, vinegar and other condiments. Comes in a special gift box made of solid Paulownia wood.

item.title: Music Box
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: With a turn the oversized metal key, Mozart’s Voi che sapete (from Marriage of Figaro) starts radiating from inside a large, solid wooden ball. This playful wind-up music box is designed by Adam + Harborth of Siebensachen, and manufactured in a village bordering the Black Forest. The 18-note mechanism is mounted in premium quality wood that has been fashioned into a perfect sphere and finished with a satin wax.
item.excerpt:encoded:
Edition #01 Snowball is a special edition Mozartkugel lacquered in white semi-matte, and accompanied by an all-white key.
Edition #03 Golden Oak is an all-new Kugel with a golden wax finish rubbed manually into the brushed oak wood. It plays “That Sounds So Glorious” from Mozart's Magic Flute, and its key is made of untreated brass.

item.title: Archiblocks
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: Archiblocks House contains 16 pieces, all machined from untreated lime-wood, then sanded by hand. Comes in three styles.
item.excerpt:encoded: Archiblocks is a construction set of building blocks created by Cinqpoints, a French maker of architectural stationery and toys, whose mission is to spread contemporary architecture to a larger audience. Smooth to touch, with precision-cut edges and angles, this inspirational collectible is designed to capture modularity, balance, and composition, with an intergenerational appeal.

item.title: Memo Block
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: The memo blocks are available in three modular sizes that form a rectangular shape when combined. Comes in white, gray, red, and a unique black option, which shows pencil marks in silver.
item.excerpt:encoded: These exquisite paper blocks, each containing 350 tear-off sheets, were created by Ito Bindery of Japan. The precision-cut edges and silky smooth surface makes these blocks perfect for taking notes, sketching out ideas, or any other purpose you can think of. Each block has a recycled paperboard base, providing stability and heft.

item.title: Coaster
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: These elegant coasters are hand-made by Mitsugu Morita of Mogu-Kagu Studios in Fukuoka, Japan. The slightly curved corner provides a graceful and whimsical characteristic, as well as making the coaster easier to grab and pick up.
item.excerpt:encoded: Crafted out of solid cherry and walnut, with an oil-based satin finish that enhances the natural color and beauty of the wood.

item.title: Pencil
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: The hexagonal design, thickness of the barrel, and warmth of the wood result in the most enjoyable pencil shape to hold. The lightly lacquered finish will wear with use and develop a beautiful patina over time. Refillable with a common 3.15mm graphite lead.
item.excerpt:encoded: These amazing writing instruments are made in Germany using timbers sourced from the Black Forest area around Baden Baden, where Wörther is located.

item.title: Cards
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: Available in Black and White.
item.excerpt:encoded: Minim is a deck of regulation playing cards re-imagined by NY-based designer Joe Doucet, who managed to successfully reduce the familiar shapes of hearts, clubs, diamonds, and spades to minimal geometric symbols. The requirement to mark the backs of regulation cards has been fulfilled by a single diagonal line instead of the traditional ornamental patterns.

item.title: Sweeper & Funnel
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: This smart design also allows for the compact cleaning duo to be hung on a hook for convenient storage, helping to avoid misplacing either piece.
item.excerpt:encoded: The everyday sweeper and dustpan, united with a twist. This versatile household item was created by Polish designer Jan Kochanski for Menu. The wooden sweeper is shaped to fit inside the hollow handle of the dustpan, which also functions as a funnel for easy disposal of the collected waste.

item.title: Nutcracker
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: Created by the Berlin-based design team Adam + Harborth, the Nusskubus provides a nut cracking experience that is practical, satisfying, and fun at the same time. Perfect for hazelnuts, walnuts, brazil nuts, and the like.
item.excerpt:encoded: This simple and sculptural nutcracker takes the act of cracking nuts back to its primitive origins by utilizing an anvil and a hammer, both made out of solid wood. Simply place a nut in one of the three craters on the anvil, and strike with the hammer cube to crack it.

item.title: Wood Cups
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: Made of castor aralia wood, these cups are meticulously shaped down to 2 mm thickness using manual methods. Handcrafted at the Takahashi Kougei wood workshop in Hokkaido, Japan.
item.excerpt:encoded: Kami means paper in Japanese, and you will understand why these cups are named Kami as soon as you touch them.

item.title: Kettle
item.dc:creator: timonto
item.content:encoded: It is a great companion to the Hario V60 ceramic coffee dripper, and can perfectly be used with other dripper brands and models.
item.excerpt:encoded: Hario Buono stainless steel kettle is the most essential tool for manual drip coffee. Its long narrow spout is designed to provide a precise flow of water, which is crucial for a good pour-over technique.
